WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.000
King Solomon's Mines

00:10.000 --> 00:29.000
Southern Africa in the year 1870

00:30.000 --> 00:32.000
Quasi!

00:32.000 --> 00:34.000
Yes, Encolo Chifka Gull.

00:34.000 --> 00:37.000
Have you found the boy, Umbupa?

00:37.000 --> 00:39.000
Yes, Encolo Chifka Gull.

00:39.000 --> 00:40.000
Bring him here!

00:40.000 --> 00:42.000
Yes, Encolo!

00:42.000 --> 00:44.000
Bring the prisoner!

00:51.000 --> 00:54.000
Are you the boy they call Umbupa?

00:54.000 --> 00:58.000
Don't dishonor me by pretending that you do not know my name!

00:58.000 --> 01:01.000
I am your chief!

01:01.000 --> 01:03.000
Call me Encolo!

01:03.000 --> 01:04.000
I will not do that!

01:04.000 --> 01:07.000
Call me Encolo!

01:07.000 --> 01:09.000
Never! You are not my chief!

01:09.000 --> 01:12.000
I am your chief!

01:12.000 --> 01:15.000
Address me as Encolo! All you will die!

01:15.000 --> 01:20.000
You are not my chief! My father, Imotou was chief!

01:20.000 --> 01:24.000
Your father is dead!

01:24.000 --> 01:26.000
So, I am chief!

01:26.000 --> 01:29.000
You are only ten years old!

01:29.000 --> 01:32.000
You are not a man!

01:32.000 --> 01:36.000
Then my uncle Quasi should rule until I am a man!

01:36.000 --> 01:38.000
Quasi!

01:38.000 --> 01:40.000
Yes, Encolo Chifka Gull.

01:40.000 --> 01:43.000
You are this boy's uncle.

01:43.000 --> 01:47.000
Who is the rightful Encolo chief of the Kukwana?

01:47.000 --> 01:50.000
You are Encolo Chifka Gull.

01:50.000 --> 01:55.000
You see, Umbupa, even your uncle is a faithful servant

01:55.000 --> 01:58.000
to the new Encolo chief.

01:58.000 --> 02:01.000
So now, you have a choice.

02:01.000 --> 02:05.000
Accept me as your Encolo chief.

02:05.000 --> 02:07.000
Or die.

02:07.000 --> 02:10.000
I will never accept you as my leader.

02:10.000 --> 02:13.000
You are not even a descendant of a chief!

02:13.000 --> 02:16.000
Kukwana Amazulu!

02:16.000 --> 02:19.000
Brothers and sisters of the Kukwana tribe!

02:19.000 --> 02:21.000
Listen to my words.

02:21.000 --> 02:24.000
My father did not die a natural death.

02:24.000 --> 02:27.000
Gagul poisoned him.

02:27.000 --> 02:28.000
I saw her do it.

02:28.000 --> 02:30.000
She is an evil witch!

02:30.000 --> 02:32.000
Stop him!

02:32.000 --> 02:34.000
I am Umbupa!

02:34.000 --> 02:36.000
Son of Imotou!

02:36.000 --> 02:39.000
But to Bupa, she do Imotou!

02:39.000 --> 02:41.000
Imotou, she do Ignose!

02:41.000 --> 02:44.000
Imotou, the son of Ignose!

02:44.000 --> 02:47.000
Silence, her boy!

02:47.000 --> 02:51.000
I am your chief! I am...

02:51.000 --> 02:55.000
Take him to Kumbabwe!

02:55.000 --> 02:57.000
And kill him!

02:57.000 --> 02:59.000
You will regret this Gagul.

02:59.000 --> 03:02.000
I will return to destroy you.

03:02.000 --> 03:04.000
No, Umbupa.

03:04.000 --> 03:07.000
You will never return.

03:07.000 --> 03:09.000
Take him away!

03:10.000 --> 03:12.000
Bupa!

03:12.000 --> 03:15.000
Bupa!

03:15.000 --> 03:18.000
Bupa! Bupa! Bupa!

03:18.000 --> 03:20.000
Here we are.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.000
Kumbabwe!

03:22.000 --> 03:24.000
The sacred mountain.

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
Umbupa?

03:26.000 --> 03:30.000
Have you made your peace with the spirits of our ancestors?

03:30.000 --> 03:33.000
I do not need to make my peace crazy.

03:33.000 --> 03:37.000
The spirits of our ancestors are on my side.

03:37.000 --> 03:42.000
But I will bring the anger of the spirits down on you and all your family.

03:42.000 --> 03:45.000
Make peace with the spirits of Umbupa! Please!

03:45.000 --> 03:47.000
You know you must do this.

03:47.000 --> 03:50.000
If you don't, your soul will never rest.

03:50.000 --> 03:52.000
You are right, Quizzy.

03:52.000 --> 03:55.000
If you kill me, my soul will never rest.

03:55.000 --> 04:01.000
I will follow you until you are dead and then your soul will have no rest.

04:01.000 --> 04:05.000
Umbupa, you are my brother's son.

04:05.000 --> 04:07.000
I know you are in Kulu.

04:07.000 --> 04:08.000
But...

04:08.000 --> 04:09.000
Wait!

04:09.000 --> 04:10.000
Yes, sir.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.000
Can you hear that?

04:12.000 --> 04:16.000
It is the sound of the spirits of our ancestors.

04:16.000 --> 04:20.000
They are telling you that what you are doing is wrong.

04:20.000 --> 04:24.000
Spirits of our Kukwana ancestors!

04:24.000 --> 04:27.000
Bupa, Bupa, Chedu, Emudu.

04:27.000 --> 04:30.000
Emudu, Chedu, Nousi.

04:30.000 --> 04:33.000
Nousi, Kukwana, Emudu.

04:33.000 --> 04:35.000
Kumbabweg is shaking.

04:35.000 --> 04:38.000
You have walking the spirits in the mountain.

04:55.000 --> 04:57.000
Quizzy?

04:57.000 --> 04:59.000
Quizzy, where are you?

04:59.000 --> 05:01.000
I'm here.

05:02.000 --> 05:03.000
I will help you.

05:03.000 --> 05:04.000
No!

05:04.000 --> 05:06.000
Umbupa, leave me.

05:06.000 --> 05:07.000
Go.

05:07.000 --> 05:09.000
Save yourself.

05:09.000 --> 05:15.000
And when the spirits tell you, come back and reclaim your tribe.

05:16.000 --> 05:18.000
You are here.

05:28.000 --> 05:34.000
Ten years later, at the house of Alan Quartermane in Durban, Southern Africa.

05:37.000 --> 05:39.000
Mr. Quartermane?

05:39.000 --> 05:41.000
Yes.

05:41.000 --> 05:43.000
I'm sorry to disturb you.

05:43.000 --> 05:47.000
I'm Sir Henwick Curtis, and this is Captain Thomas Godwin.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.000
Please to meet you, Quartermane.

05:49.000 --> 05:51.000
Heard a lot about you.

05:51.000 --> 05:56.000
Mr. Quartermane, there's a matter of some importance that we wish to speak to you.

05:56.000 --> 06:02.000
I'm afraid I've only this minute arrived from Cape Town, and I long journey, certainly.

06:02.000 --> 06:05.000
But we have come from London.

06:05.000 --> 06:06.000
From London?

06:06.000 --> 06:07.000
Yes.

06:08.000 --> 06:10.000
All right.

06:10.000 --> 06:12.000
Let's talk on the veranda.

06:12.000 --> 06:15.000
Florence, bring drinks for my guests.

06:18.000 --> 06:21.000
You'll have a very beautiful home, Mr. Quartermane.

06:21.000 --> 06:23.000
Thank you, Sir Henwick.

06:23.000 --> 06:26.000
Now, would you mind telling me the reason for your visit?

06:26.000 --> 06:31.000
Before I answer that question, Mr. Quartermane, may I ask you something?

06:31.000 --> 06:36.000
About this time last year, you were in the north of Transval.

06:36.000 --> 06:37.000
Am I right?

06:37.000 --> 06:38.000
Yes.

06:38.000 --> 06:41.000
Near the Lukango River beyond Matabili.

06:41.000 --> 06:42.000
Yes.

06:42.000 --> 06:44.000
How did you know that?

06:44.000 --> 06:45.000
What were you doing there?

06:45.000 --> 06:47.000
I was hunting elephants.

06:47.000 --> 06:48.000
It's what I do.

06:48.000 --> 06:50.000
I'm an ivory trader.

06:50.000 --> 06:51.000
But I'm sorry.

06:51.000 --> 06:53.000
Why all these questions?

06:53.000 --> 06:56.000
Mr. Quartermane, I will explain.

06:56.000 --> 06:58.000
But one last question.

06:58.000 --> 07:03.000
Last year at Matabili, did you meet a man called George Neville?

07:03.000 --> 07:05.000
George Neville?

07:05.000 --> 07:07.000
Are George Neville?

07:07.000 --> 07:09.000
Yes, I did.

07:09.000 --> 07:11.000
When was the last time you saw him?

07:11.000 --> 07:12.000
A year ago.

07:12.000 --> 07:14.000
At the time you're referring to.

07:14.000 --> 07:16.000
I haven't seen him since then.

07:16.000 --> 07:18.000
Do you know what happened to him?

07:18.000 --> 07:22.000
Can I once again ask the reason for these questions?

07:22.000 --> 07:26.000
I'm here in Africa because I want to find George Neville.

07:26.000 --> 07:28.000
He is my brother.

07:28.000 --> 07:29.000
Your brother?

07:29.000 --> 07:32.000
But Neville is not his real name.

07:32.000 --> 07:35.000
His real name is George Curtis.

07:35.000 --> 07:36.000
I see.

07:36.000 --> 07:38.000
The thing is, Quartermane.

07:38.000 --> 07:46.000
George Curtis left England a year ago with a ridiculous plan to come to Africa to look for a diamond mine.

07:46.000 --> 07:50.000
He booked a passage to Cape Town and hasn't been heard of since.

07:50.000 --> 07:51.000
I see.

07:51.000 --> 07:53.000
Captain Godwin.

07:53.000 --> 07:56.000
What is your interest in this matter, if I may ask?

07:56.000 --> 07:59.000
George Curtis is married to my sister.

07:59.000 --> 08:04.000
They left her and their two children in England to go off from this ridiculous adventure.

08:04.000 --> 08:10.000
So, for the second time of asking, have you any idea what his plan was?

08:10.000 --> 08:13.000
Well, you're right.

08:13.000 --> 08:19.000
Neville, your brother, was looking for a diamond mine.

08:19.000 --> 08:25.000
He told me he intended to search for a place which is known as King Solomon's Mine.

08:25.000 --> 08:28.000
So, it's true.

08:28.000 --> 08:32.000
This is what I heard, but what are King Solomon's Mines?

08:32.000 --> 08:44.000
King Solomon's Mines, if they exist, are said to contain more and better diamonds than any mines in Africa or indeed the world.

08:44.000 --> 08:45.000
Really?

08:45.000 --> 08:48.000
Where are they, Captain Godwin?

08:48.000 --> 08:55.000
If people knew the exact location of King Solomon's Mines, they would have been discovered long before now.

08:55.000 --> 08:57.000
No one knows.

08:57.000 --> 09:00.000
They do know where they are said to be.

09:00.000 --> 09:01.000
Where?

09:01.000 --> 09:06.000
They are said to be in the Suleiman Mountains to the north of Matabili.

09:06.000 --> 09:08.000
And that's where the name comes from.

09:08.000 --> 09:09.000
Suleiman.

09:09.000 --> 09:11.000
Solomon, you see?

09:11.000 --> 09:13.000
Nothing to do with King Solomon at all.

09:13.000 --> 09:14.000
I see.

09:14.000 --> 09:19.000
So, when you were in Matabili, you were close to these mountains?

09:19.000 --> 09:20.000
Not at all.

09:20.000 --> 09:25.000
A few miles beyond the Lukanga River, there's nothing but desert.

09:25.000 --> 09:28.000
The Kukwana Desert, it's called.

09:28.000 --> 09:31.000
The Suleiman Mountains are beyond the desert.

09:31.000 --> 09:32.000
I see.

09:32.000 --> 09:36.000
Have you ever crossed the Kukwana Desert?

09:36.000 --> 09:38.000
Cross the Kukwana Desert?

09:38.000 --> 09:41.000
Sanri, only a madman would try to do that.

09:41.000 --> 09:42.000
Why?

09:42.000 --> 09:43.000
Is it too big?

09:43.000 --> 09:48.000
It is indeed big, but the size of the desert is not the problem.

09:48.000 --> 09:50.000
There are other reasons too.

09:51.000 --> 09:55.000
The Kukwana Desert is named after the Kukwana tribe.

09:55.000 --> 09:59.000
The desert and the Suleiman Mountains are their homeland.

09:59.000 --> 10:06.000
They believe that the area is a spirit world inhabited by their ancestors.

10:06.000 --> 10:13.000
Mr. Quarterman, as far as you are aware, has any white man ever crossed the Kukwana Desert?

10:13.000 --> 10:16.000
I only know of one.

10:16.000 --> 10:20.000
Who was that? A man called Jose Silvestre.

10:20.000 --> 10:22.000
Do you know him?

10:22.000 --> 10:23.000
I met him.

10:23.000 --> 10:25.000
Do you know where we can find him?

10:25.000 --> 10:27.000
I'm afraid he's dead.

10:27.000 --> 10:30.000
Oh, I'm sorry. What happened to him?

10:30.000 --> 10:35.000
Well, I will tell you what I know.

10:35.000 --> 10:44.000
About two years ago, I was at a miserable godforsaken place on the Lukanga River, called Sitanda's Crown.

10:44.000 --> 10:47.000
While I was there, I fell ill.

10:47.000 --> 10:51.000
A fever. I could hardly move for three weeks.

10:51.000 --> 10:55.000
Sitanda's crawl is not a place that many white people reach,

10:55.000 --> 11:01.000
so I was surprised one day when a European was shown into my tent.

11:01.000 --> 11:04.000
It turned out he was Portuguese.

11:08.000 --> 11:10.000
Mr. Quarterman.

11:11.000 --> 11:13.000
Who are you?

11:13.000 --> 11:15.000
What do you want?

11:15.000 --> 11:17.000
My name is Jose Silvestre.

11:17.000 --> 11:20.000
What are you doing at Sitanda's Crown?

11:20.000 --> 11:22.000
I need your help.

11:22.000 --> 11:23.000
What for?

11:23.000 --> 11:26.000
I want to find King Solomon's diamond mines.

11:26.000 --> 11:29.000
King Solomon's mines?

11:32.000 --> 11:35.000
Don't make me laugh. It hurts.

11:35.000 --> 11:37.000
You find the idea amusing.

11:37.000 --> 11:39.000
Of course I do.

11:39.000 --> 11:43.000
No one has ever found King Solomon's mines.

11:43.000 --> 11:45.000
They probably don't exist.

11:45.000 --> 11:48.000
This is what I believe too.

11:48.000 --> 11:51.000
Until I was given this.

11:57.000 --> 12:00.000
What was it? What did he have?

12:00.000 --> 12:03.000
A map. A map?

12:03.000 --> 12:06.000
Giving the location of King Solomon's mines.

12:07.000 --> 12:09.000
Did you think it was genuine?

12:09.000 --> 12:11.000
No. Of course not.

12:11.000 --> 12:13.000
Not at the time.

12:13.000 --> 12:16.000
Anyway, Silvestre could see that I was ill

12:16.000 --> 12:19.000
and that he wasn't going to persuade me to join him,

12:19.000 --> 12:24.000
so he set off with just a servant to accompany him.

12:24.000 --> 12:27.000
To be honest, I forgot all about him.

12:27.000 --> 12:30.000
But then, about two weeks later,

12:30.000 --> 12:34.000
there was suddenly a lot of shouting outside my tent.

12:35.000 --> 12:37.000
What is it?

12:37.000 --> 12:40.000
It is the man who was here before Massa.

12:40.000 --> 12:43.000
What? The Portuguese, chap?

12:43.000 --> 12:45.000
I do not know Massa.

12:45.000 --> 12:47.000
What the man?

12:47.000 --> 12:49.000
Are you there?

12:49.000 --> 12:51.000
What the man?

12:51.000 --> 12:55.000
God, Silvestre, what the devil has happened to you?

12:55.000 --> 12:57.000
What the man?

12:57.000 --> 13:00.000
I was there.

13:00.000 --> 13:03.000
I saw King Solomon's mines.

13:03.000 --> 13:06.000
But the kukwana came after me,

13:06.000 --> 13:08.000
and I had no water.

13:08.000 --> 13:10.000
But they are there.

13:10.000 --> 13:13.000
What the man? I saw them.

13:13.000 --> 13:18.000
Calm down, man. Take it easy.

13:18.000 --> 13:21.000
Poor man.

13:21.000 --> 13:24.000
Sir, did he find the mines?

13:24.000 --> 13:26.000
Do you think?

13:26.000 --> 13:28.000
I don't know for sure.

13:28.000 --> 13:30.000
But at what?

13:30.000 --> 13:33.000
In his bag, I found the map.

13:33.000 --> 13:35.000
And some diamonds.

13:35.000 --> 13:37.000
Do you have the map?

13:37.000 --> 13:40.000
Yes. Can we see it?

13:40.000 --> 13:43.000
I'll go and get it.

13:44.000 --> 13:46.000
I'll go and get it.

13:53.000 --> 13:56.000
So, this is the desert,

13:56.000 --> 13:58.000
and beyond the desert,

13:58.000 --> 14:01.000
here are the Suleiman Mountains.

14:01.000 --> 14:03.000
According to this map,

14:03.000 --> 14:06.000
there are forests and plenty of fresh water,

14:06.000 --> 14:10.000
and this mountain here is called Kong Badway.

14:10.000 --> 14:14.000
I discovered that this is kukwana for sacred mountain.

14:14.000 --> 14:17.000
The mines seem to be somewhere on this mountain.

14:17.000 --> 14:19.000
I see.

14:19.000 --> 14:21.000
Did you show this map to my brother?

14:21.000 --> 14:24.000
No, I didn't have it with me when I met him.

14:24.000 --> 14:26.000
But did you tell him about it?

14:26.000 --> 14:27.000
Yes.

14:27.000 --> 14:30.000
And I told him what happened to Sylvestere too.

14:30.000 --> 14:33.000
I told him he was mad to try and find the mines.

14:33.000 --> 14:36.000
Sir Henry, buy the map from Courtomaine,

14:36.000 --> 14:39.000
then we can find some natives to guide us and we can get there ourselves.

14:40.000 --> 14:43.000
You think it's that easy, do you?

14:43.000 --> 14:46.000
Well, I wish you the best of luck.

14:46.000 --> 14:49.000
No, it will definitely not be easy.

14:49.000 --> 14:53.000
I know that, but one thing I do know, Mr. Courtomaine,

14:53.000 --> 14:58.000
I'm sure that you are the only person who can help us find my brother.

14:58.000 --> 14:59.000
Me?

14:59.000 --> 15:02.000
Well, I am also a very rich man,

15:02.000 --> 15:05.000
and I will pay you not just to let me have the map,

15:05.000 --> 15:09.000
but also to accompany us to the Solomon Mountains.

15:09.000 --> 15:14.000
Sir Henry, I will accompany you on one condition.

15:14.000 --> 15:15.000
Name your condition.

15:15.000 --> 15:19.000
I have a son who lives in London.

15:19.000 --> 15:21.000
He studies medicine.

15:21.000 --> 15:25.000
He depends on me for money so that he can continue his studies.

15:25.000 --> 15:28.000
If anything happens to me,

15:28.000 --> 15:32.000
I want to make sure that he completes them.

15:32.000 --> 15:34.000
So be it.

15:34.000 --> 15:38.000
I will send a telegram to my solicitor in London tomorrow.

15:38.000 --> 15:44.000
I will arrange that your son can complete his medical training at my expense

15:44.000 --> 15:47.000
in the event of anything happening to you.

15:47.000 --> 15:49.000
Oh, to me.

15:49.000 --> 15:51.000
Now, will you accompany us?

15:51.000 --> 15:53.000
Yes, good man.

15:53.000 --> 15:54.000
Excellent.

15:54.000 --> 15:57.000
We will start making preparations tomorrow.

15:57.000 --> 15:59.000
Leave that to me.

15:59.000 --> 16:03.000
I know where to get what we need and how to get the best price.

16:03.000 --> 16:06.000
But I will tell you now.

16:06.000 --> 16:10.000
We have as much chance of surviving an attempt to reach the Solomon Mountains

16:10.000 --> 16:12.000
as that man Silvestre.

16:18.000 --> 16:19.000
Good morning, Alan.

16:19.000 --> 16:21.000
Good morning, Sir Henry.

16:21.000 --> 16:23.000
How are preparations for the journey?

16:23.000 --> 16:25.000
Not good, I'm afraid.

16:25.000 --> 16:28.000
I have the wagons that we need and the provisions,

16:28.000 --> 16:32.000
but I can't find servants who are prepared to travel with us.

16:32.000 --> 16:34.000
I have a driver.

16:34.000 --> 16:36.000
His name is Gozer and he's a good man,

16:36.000 --> 16:41.000
but he's only prepared to come with us as far as Sitanda's crawl.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.000
He won't cross the Kukawana desert.

16:43.000 --> 16:44.000
Don't worry.

16:44.000 --> 16:45.000
I have found someone.

16:45.000 --> 16:47.000
Two men, in fact.

16:47.000 --> 16:48.000
You have.

16:48.000 --> 16:50.000
Did you tell them where we are going?

16:50.000 --> 16:51.000
Yes, of course.

16:51.000 --> 16:55.000
I told them we were going to the Solomon Mountains to look for my brother.

16:55.000 --> 16:58.000
They seem like good, strong men.

16:58.000 --> 17:00.000
One of them is rather quiet,

17:00.000 --> 17:03.000
but the other is a very intelligent man.

17:03.000 --> 17:05.000
He speaks English well, too.

17:05.000 --> 17:08.000
Of course, you must have the final decision quarter-main,

17:08.000 --> 17:10.000
so I have brought them here this morning.

17:10.000 --> 17:12.000
Here, yes.

17:12.000 --> 17:14.000
They are waiting outside.

17:14.000 --> 17:17.000
Would you be so kind as to speak to them?

17:17.000 --> 17:18.000
Certainly.

17:26.000 --> 17:28.000
These are the men.

17:28.000 --> 17:29.000
I see.

17:29.000 --> 17:30.000
Do you speak English?

17:30.000 --> 17:31.000
Yes, Master.

17:31.000 --> 17:32.000
And you?

17:32.000 --> 17:34.000
Yes, Master.

17:34.000 --> 17:38.000
You know that we are planning to travel across the Kukawana desert

17:38.000 --> 17:40.000
and into the Solomon Mountains?

17:40.000 --> 17:41.000
Yes, Master.

17:41.000 --> 17:43.000
We are Kukawana.

17:43.000 --> 17:45.000
We know those lands.

17:45.000 --> 17:49.000
Have you heard of the place we call King Solomon's Mines?

17:49.000 --> 17:50.000
Yes, Master.

17:50.000 --> 17:52.000
Do you know where they are?

17:52.000 --> 17:54.000
No one knows where they are, Master.

17:55.000 --> 17:56.000
I see.

17:56.000 --> 17:58.000
What are your names?

17:58.000 --> 18:00.000
This man is Kiva.

18:00.000 --> 18:01.000
And you?

18:01.000 --> 18:02.000
I...

18:02.000 --> 18:04.000
I am Ubopa.

18:07.000 --> 18:10.000
So it was that six of us departed for the north.

18:10.000 --> 18:14.000
So Henry, Captain Godwin and myself,

18:14.000 --> 18:18.000
goes to the driver, Kiva and Umbopa.

18:18.000 --> 18:21.000
It was a journey of a thousand miles.

18:21.000 --> 18:26.000
It was the second week in March before we made camp near Sitanda's Crow.

18:26.000 --> 18:29.000
We left Goza with one wagon there,

18:29.000 --> 18:33.000
and the five of us set off towards the Kukawana desert.

18:34.000 --> 18:36.000
Umbopa and Kiva led the Oxen,

18:36.000 --> 18:55.000
and Sir Henry, Captain Godwin and I followed with our rifles at the ready.

18:55.000 --> 18:59.000
It was then that I noticed some marks on Umbopa's back.

18:59.000 --> 19:02.000
They looked as if they had been made with a knife.

19:03.000 --> 19:04.000
Umbopa?

19:04.000 --> 19:05.000
Yes, Master.

19:05.000 --> 19:08.000
What are those marks on your back?

19:08.000 --> 19:11.000
It looks as if you had a fight with a lion.

19:12.000 --> 19:13.000
No, Master.

19:13.000 --> 19:16.000
I don't think I would leave to tell you about that.

19:16.000 --> 19:23.000
Whatever the marks were, Umbopa was quite clearly not planning to tell us about them.

19:24.000 --> 19:32.000
That night, we made camp near the river for the last time.

19:37.000 --> 19:41.000
The next morning, we had to turn north towards the desert.

19:41.000 --> 19:44.000
I woke early and started preparing to leave.

19:44.000 --> 19:50.000
When I went to wake the others, there was no sign of Captain Godwin.

19:50.000 --> 19:51.000
Kiva!

19:52.000 --> 19:54.000
Yes, Master.

19:54.000 --> 19:56.000
Where is Captain Godwin?

19:56.000 --> 19:58.000
He went into the forest, Master.

19:58.000 --> 20:01.000
I tell him there are elephants, so he went to sea.

20:01.000 --> 20:03.000
Oh, my God.

20:03.000 --> 20:05.000
The man's a fool.

20:05.000 --> 20:10.000
Go and find him and tell him to come back immediately.

20:13.000 --> 20:15.000
What on earth was that?

20:15.000 --> 20:16.000
I don't know.

20:16.000 --> 20:17.000
Umbopa?

20:17.000 --> 20:18.000
Yes, Master.

20:18.000 --> 20:21.000
Go and find out what is going on.

20:21.000 --> 20:22.000
Yes, Master.

20:35.000 --> 20:37.000
What in God's name is happening?

20:37.000 --> 20:40.000
I don't know, but we'd better find out.

20:40.000 --> 20:41.000
Come on.

20:41.000 --> 20:45.000
Sir Henry and I began running in the direction of the noise.

20:49.000 --> 20:54.000
It was clear that Sir Henry hadn't run anywhere for a while.

20:54.000 --> 20:57.000
I was soon a long way ahead of him.

20:57.000 --> 21:00.000
Then I saw Godwin running towards me.

21:00.000 --> 21:04.000
Godwin, what the hell is going on?

21:04.000 --> 21:07.000
I shot an elephant.

21:07.000 --> 21:09.000
You did what?

21:09.000 --> 21:12.000
I couldn't stop myself.

21:12.000 --> 21:14.000
It was feeding.

21:14.000 --> 21:16.000
It was a sitting target.

21:16.000 --> 21:19.000
But I only wounded it.

21:19.000 --> 21:22.000
You fool!

21:22.000 --> 21:25.000
He made a dreadful noise and ran towards me.

21:25.000 --> 21:27.000
Then Kiva arrived.

21:27.000 --> 21:31.000
He started shouting and running across the elephant's path.

21:31.000 --> 21:34.000
It turned and went for him.

21:34.000 --> 21:37.000
He tore him to pieces.

21:37.000 --> 21:39.000
I'm sorry.

21:39.000 --> 21:42.000
I think he's dead.

21:43.000 --> 21:46.000
When buried Kiva in the forest,

21:46.000 --> 21:49.000
Umbooper said a few words in Kukwana,

21:49.000 --> 21:52.000
then turned and spoke to us.

21:54.000 --> 21:57.000
Kiva was the bravest of brave men.

21:57.000 --> 21:59.000
Here, here.

21:59.000 --> 22:02.000
Captain Godwin, Kiva saved your life.

22:02.000 --> 22:05.000
But you have done something very bad.

22:05.000 --> 22:07.000
I know that.

22:07.000 --> 22:09.000
It is worse than you think.

22:09.000 --> 22:12.000
Kiva was a Kukwana, and you caused his death.

22:12.000 --> 22:15.000
We are already on Kukwana land.

22:15.000 --> 22:17.000
You have raised the spirits of our ancestors.

22:17.000 --> 22:20.000
You must not anger the spirits again.

22:33.000 --> 22:37.000
Later that day, we finally reached the Kukwana desert.

22:37.000 --> 22:40.000
It stretched out in front of us.

22:40.000 --> 22:44.000
Crossing it seemed an impossible and foolish task.

22:44.000 --> 22:49.000
After three days, we could see the mountains in the distance.

22:49.000 --> 22:53.000
Then, on the fourth day...

22:53.000 --> 22:55.000
Sir Henry.

22:55.000 --> 22:56.000
Court men.

22:56.000 --> 22:58.000
Look.

22:58.000 --> 23:00.000
What is it, Godwin?

23:00.000 --> 23:01.000
Look.

23:01.000 --> 23:02.000
Street ahead.

23:02.000 --> 23:03.000
Trees.

23:03.000 --> 23:05.000
Thank God.

23:05.000 --> 23:07.000
Trees means water.

23:07.000 --> 23:11.000
In less than an hour, we reached the trees.

23:11.000 --> 23:16.000
The good news was that there was a small lake and a forest beyond it.

23:16.000 --> 23:22.000
We all threw ourselves into the water, drinking and washing the sand off our faces.

23:24.000 --> 23:28.000
The bad news was that we were not alone.

23:28.000 --> 23:32.000
Godwin was the first to notice that we were being watched.

23:32.000 --> 23:38.000
On the edge of the forest stood a group of natives, about 30 of them.

23:38.000 --> 23:44.000
Most of them were carrying Asagai, the spears that make them such frightened warriors.

23:44.000 --> 23:50.000
One of them shouted something, and as one, they charged towards us.

23:57.000 --> 24:00.000
Godwin ran to the wagon and picked up a rifle.

24:00.000 --> 24:02.000
Stop or I shoot!

24:02.000 --> 24:08.000
The natives had clearly never seen a rifle before, so they didn't stop charging towards us.

24:08.000 --> 24:09.000
Then...

24:14.000 --> 24:17.000
One of them fell to the ground, wounded.

24:17.000 --> 24:21.000
The others stopped, then began to charge again.

24:21.000 --> 24:35.000
I thought we were all as good as dead, but then Umbopa stepped in front of the natives and began shouting at them.

24:35.000 --> 24:39.000
To my amazement, they stopped and listened to him.

24:52.000 --> 24:56.000
Kortonane, to understand what he's saying, not sure.

24:56.000 --> 25:04.000
I think he's telling them that he's the son of someone called Ignosin, who is the son of the Great Chief Imotto.

25:04.000 --> 25:25.340
At this point, something extraordinary happened.

25:25.340 --> 25:30.820
Umbopa turned his back on the natives, and three of them walked towards him.

25:30.820 --> 25:33.180
Godwin raised his gun again.

25:33.180 --> 25:40.900
Godwin looked astonished, but did as he was told, the natives looked at the marks on Umbopa's

25:40.900 --> 25:41.900
back.

25:41.900 --> 25:59.420
To my absolute astonishment, the natives threw their asagai away and fell to the ground,

25:59.420 --> 26:06.980
as if praying at Umbopa's feet.

26:06.980 --> 26:11.020
It was some time before any of us could speak.

26:11.020 --> 26:15.220
Sir Henry was the first to try to find out what was happening.

26:15.220 --> 26:18.820
Umbopa, who do you mind telling us what's going on?

26:18.820 --> 26:25.260
These men are Kukwana warriors, but they have been banished from their tribal home, because

26:25.260 --> 26:31.260
they criticize the woman who calls herself in Kulu chief of the Kukwana.

26:31.260 --> 26:33.260
They are outlaws.

26:33.260 --> 26:37.020
If they go back, they will have to fight for their lives.

26:37.020 --> 26:42.060
Thanks to the spirits of our ancestors, we have found each other.

26:42.060 --> 26:45.500
What do you mean found each other?

26:45.500 --> 26:50.500
Since they were banished, they have searched these lands for their true leader.

26:50.500 --> 26:52.820
I am their true leader.

26:52.820 --> 26:53.820
You?

26:53.820 --> 26:54.820
What?

26:54.820 --> 26:58.660
I am the true chief of the Kukwana.

26:58.660 --> 27:06.660
Ten years ago, my father was killed, poisoned by an evil woman, Gagul, who now calls herself

27:06.660 --> 27:08.620
in Kulu chief.

27:08.620 --> 27:14.260
She tried to kill me too, but the spirits of our ancestors know this.

27:14.260 --> 27:16.780
And these men know this story too.

27:16.780 --> 27:19.100
They have been searching for me.

27:19.100 --> 27:26.340
Pardon me for doubting you, Umbopa, but how do these men know that you are their chief?

27:26.340 --> 27:31.820
Because of the marks on my back, only the son of a chief has these marks.

27:31.820 --> 27:35.900
Now these men will follow and obey me, and I must lead them.

27:35.900 --> 27:36.900
Lead them?

27:36.900 --> 27:38.100
Where?

27:38.100 --> 27:43.060
It is time for me to take my place as in Kulu chief of my tribe.

27:43.060 --> 27:45.900
They have a leader who is not the true in Kulu.

27:45.900 --> 27:49.820
I must fight her men in battle and defeat them.

27:49.820 --> 27:54.620
Tomorrow, we will leave to do battle with Gagul and her men.

27:54.620 --> 27:57.340
Leave, but what about us?

27:57.340 --> 28:00.860
You promised to help us find George Curtis?

28:00.860 --> 28:03.100
No, Captain Daudwing.

28:03.100 --> 28:06.420
I promised to lead you to the Suleiman Mountains.

28:06.420 --> 28:08.780
This I have done.

28:08.780 --> 28:11.620
I have also saved all of your lives.

28:11.620 --> 28:14.180
Without me, you would all be dead now.

28:14.180 --> 28:20.300
Thomas, please, for once in your life, listen, Umbopa.

28:20.300 --> 28:25.300
I understand what you want to do, but we still need your help.

28:25.300 --> 28:30.340
We have to find King Solomon's minds and see if my brother is there.

28:30.340 --> 28:34.980
I need to know if he came here and if anyone saw him.

28:34.980 --> 28:43.700
Wait, I will talk to my people.

28:43.700 --> 28:46.660
For some minutes, he returned.

28:46.660 --> 28:51.580
Sir Henry, I asked the men if they had seen a white man here.

28:51.580 --> 28:53.300
What did they say?

28:53.300 --> 28:55.460
Use your brother, a tall man.

28:55.460 --> 28:57.620
Yes, very tall.

28:57.620 --> 29:00.100
A tall white man was here last year.

29:00.100 --> 29:03.780
He had one finger missing from this hand.

29:03.780 --> 29:05.580
His left hand.

29:05.580 --> 29:07.540
Yes, that's right.

29:07.540 --> 29:09.100
It's George.

29:09.100 --> 29:10.500
Where did they see him?

29:10.500 --> 29:12.100
Where did he go?

29:12.100 --> 29:14.700
They think he was captured by Gagua's men.

29:14.700 --> 29:17.700
Oh, God, no.

29:17.700 --> 29:19.460
And then what?

29:19.460 --> 29:24.180
They took him to Kongbabwe, the tall mountain you can see over there.

29:24.180 --> 29:27.580
Kongbabwe, sacred mountain.

29:27.580 --> 29:29.380
That's where the mines are.

29:29.380 --> 29:32.660
Umbopa, we must go there.

29:32.660 --> 29:34.380
Very well.

29:34.380 --> 29:39.060
But you must know that Kongbabwe is a sacred place for us.

29:39.060 --> 29:42.740
It is the resting place of the spirits of our chiefs.

29:42.740 --> 29:45.540
It is dangerous for you to go there.

29:45.540 --> 29:50.260
When the spirits are angry, Kongbabwe also becomes angry.

29:50.260 --> 29:52.380
But we have to go there.

29:52.380 --> 29:55.980
We have to find out what happened to my brother.

29:55.980 --> 29:59.620
You will never find your way to Kongbabwe alone.

29:59.620 --> 30:02.020
You will get lost in the forest.

30:02.020 --> 30:04.820
I will tell one of the men to go with you.

30:04.820 --> 30:05.820
Achata!

30:05.820 --> 30:07.100
Enkulu Umbopa.

30:07.100 --> 30:09.420
This man is my father's brother.

30:09.420 --> 30:10.820
His name is Kwezi.

30:10.820 --> 30:15.140
So he is also a descendant of the great chief, Emoto.

30:15.140 --> 30:18.980
He will lead you to Kongbabwe and Korna Suleiman.

30:18.980 --> 30:26.300
Korna Suleiman, Suleiman Cave, the place you call King Solomon's mines.

30:26.300 --> 30:29.540
So you know where it is.

30:38.100 --> 30:45.100
The next morning, we set off through the dense tropical forest towards Kongbabwe.

30:45.100 --> 30:49.100
There was no path and the walk was hard.

30:49.100 --> 30:51.100
But Kwezi knew the way.

30:51.100 --> 30:56.100
We walked for hours until we found ourselves at the foot of the mountain.

30:56.100 --> 31:00.100
After a short rest, we began to climb.

31:00.100 --> 31:05.100
Suddenly, Kwezi stopped in front of a pile of rocks.

31:06.100 --> 31:09.100
This is Korna Suleiman, please help me.

31:09.100 --> 31:15.100
Kwezi indicated that we had to move the rocks, so we all began to pull at them.

31:15.100 --> 31:18.100
They were large rocks and it was hard work.

31:18.100 --> 31:22.100
Eventually, we could see a dark cave.

31:22.100 --> 31:25.100
It's time to light the torches.

31:25.100 --> 31:29.100
We lit torches and walked into the cave.

31:29.100 --> 31:34.100
It was dark and damp and looked like any other cave.

31:36.100 --> 31:39.100
We walked further and further.

31:39.100 --> 31:46.100
Then suddenly, the light from the torches began to reflect on diamonds.

31:46.100 --> 31:49.100
Hundreds of them.

31:49.100 --> 31:51.100
Some were on the ground.

31:51.100 --> 31:55.100
Others were still in the rock on the walls of the cave.

31:55.100 --> 31:57.100
My God!

31:57.100 --> 31:59.100
Look at all these diamonds!

31:59.100 --> 32:03.100
We have to take some of them with us, Korna Man.

32:03.100 --> 32:07.100
Korna Man, where are you?

32:07.100 --> 32:11.100
I had walked on ahead of the others and I saw something.

32:11.100 --> 32:13.100
I'm over here.

32:13.100 --> 32:16.100
Sir Henry, I think you should come here.

32:16.100 --> 32:19.100
I'm coming.

32:19.100 --> 32:21.100
What is this?

32:21.100 --> 32:22.100
Look.

32:22.100 --> 32:23.100
Where?

32:23.100 --> 32:25.100
What can you see?

32:25.100 --> 32:27.100
Down below.

32:27.100 --> 32:28.100
Down there.

32:28.100 --> 32:29.100
Look.

32:29.100 --> 32:31.100
There's something there.

32:31.100 --> 32:33.100
I can't see anything.

32:33.100 --> 32:37.100
I think, I think, it's a skeleton.

32:37.100 --> 32:38.100
A skeleton?

32:38.100 --> 32:40.100
Dear God.

32:40.100 --> 32:43.100
I'll climb down and have a closer look.

32:47.100 --> 32:49.100
Be careful, Godwin.

32:49.100 --> 32:51.100
The rocks look dangerous.

32:51.100 --> 32:54.100
I'm all right.

32:54.100 --> 32:56.100
Oh my God.

32:56.100 --> 33:00.100
It is a skeleton and...

33:01.100 --> 33:05.100
Sir Henry, I'm afraid it's bad news.

33:05.100 --> 33:08.100
There is no middle finger on the left hand.

33:08.100 --> 33:10.100
It's George.

33:10.100 --> 33:12.100
Oh no.

33:12.100 --> 33:16.100
Please, God, I hope his death wasn't too violent.

33:16.100 --> 33:18.100
Korna Man, do you think we can...

33:18.100 --> 33:19.100
Shh, quiet.

33:19.100 --> 33:21.100
Listen.

33:21.100 --> 33:23.100
What on earth is that noise?

33:23.100 --> 33:25.100
It's an earth tremor.

33:25.100 --> 33:26.100
Quick.

33:26.100 --> 33:28.100
We have to get out.

33:28.100 --> 33:30.100
What's happening?

33:30.100 --> 33:32.100
Godwin, it's an earth tremor.

33:32.100 --> 33:34.100
Climb back up.

33:34.100 --> 33:36.100
We have to get out.

33:36.100 --> 33:38.100
I can't hear you.

33:38.100 --> 33:40.100
Look out!

33:52.100 --> 33:53.100
What's happening?

33:53.100 --> 33:55.100
I can't see a thing.

33:55.100 --> 33:57.100
There was a rock form.

33:57.100 --> 33:59.100
Godwin's buried.

33:59.100 --> 34:01.100
We must try to get him out of there.

34:01.100 --> 34:03.100
Are you mad?

34:03.100 --> 34:05.100
Tons of rock just fell on him.

34:05.100 --> 34:08.100
He didn't have a chance of surviving that.

34:08.100 --> 34:10.100
We have to get out.

34:10.100 --> 34:13.100
The whole cave is falling down.

34:13.100 --> 34:15.100
Come on!

34:22.100 --> 34:25.100
The entrance to the cave has disappeared.

34:25.100 --> 34:26.100
We're trapped.

34:26.100 --> 34:28.100
We have to find another way out.

34:28.100 --> 34:29.100
But look.

34:29.100 --> 34:31.100
Over there.

34:31.100 --> 34:33.100
There's a kind of tunnel in the rock.

34:33.100 --> 34:35.100
It may be a way out.

34:35.100 --> 34:42.100
I put down my torch and began to crawl into the dark tunnel of rock.

34:42.100 --> 34:44.100
It was a small space.

34:44.100 --> 34:47.100
And as I crawled through it, it got even narrower.

34:47.100 --> 34:51.100
I felt like a rat in a drain pipe.

34:51.100 --> 34:54.100
And I was beginning to panic.

34:54.100 --> 34:56.100
But I could breathe.

34:56.100 --> 34:58.100
Air was coming from somewhere.

34:58.100 --> 35:02.100
The space began to get wider.

35:02.100 --> 35:05.100
And soon, I was able to stand up.

35:05.100 --> 35:10.100
In front of me, there was another entrance to the cave.

35:10.100 --> 35:14.100
Soon, Sir Henry emerged from the tunnel behind me.

35:14.100 --> 35:16.100
We were safe.

35:25.100 --> 35:28.100
God be praised.

35:28.100 --> 35:30.100
Well done, Courtney.

35:30.100 --> 35:34.100
I thought we were going to die in there, Sir Henry.

35:34.100 --> 35:37.100
I think we are still in trouble.

35:37.100 --> 35:38.100
What?

35:38.100 --> 35:39.100
Why?

35:39.100 --> 35:40.100
Look.

35:40.100 --> 35:44.100
Outside the cave, there was a band of natives.

35:44.100 --> 35:47.100
But they were not Umbopa's warriors.

35:47.100 --> 35:51.100
Leading them was a tall, fierce woman.

35:52.100 --> 35:59.100
I realized to my horror that we must be in the presence of the evil chief, Gagul.

35:59.100 --> 36:04.100
White men, you have entered the Kona Solomon.

36:04.100 --> 36:08.100
And you have woken the anger of our ancestors.

36:08.100 --> 36:11.100
You will die for this.

36:11.100 --> 36:13.100
Kill them!

36:13.100 --> 36:16.100
There seemed no way to escape now.

36:16.100 --> 36:20.100
I was convinced that these were the last moments of my life.

36:20.100 --> 36:29.100
But then, suddenly, Umbopa appeared behind Gagul alone.

36:29.100 --> 36:31.100
Gagul!

36:31.100 --> 36:34.100
Who are you?

36:34.100 --> 36:41.100
I am Umbopa, in Kolo Chief of the Kukwana.

36:41.100 --> 36:43.100
Umbopa.

36:43.100 --> 36:45.100
Impossible.

36:45.100 --> 36:47.100
Umbopa is dead.

36:47.100 --> 36:49.100
No, Gagul.

36:50.100 --> 36:52.100
You killed my father.

36:52.100 --> 36:54.100
But you could not kill me.

36:54.100 --> 36:59.100
The spirit saved me and brought me back here to defeat you.

36:59.100 --> 37:02.100
You will never defeat me.

37:02.100 --> 37:05.100
No one will defeat me.

37:05.100 --> 37:07.100
Kill him.

37:07.100 --> 37:08.100
Now!

37:08.100 --> 37:13.100
Before Gagul's men could meet Umbopa.

37:13.100 --> 37:18.100
Crazy and the other outlaws appeared behind them.

37:18.100 --> 37:24.100
Gagul's men were taken by surprise and were killed or taken prisoner almost immediately.

37:24.100 --> 37:32.100
Two of Umbopa's warriors held Gagul and another was about to drive an Asagai through her heart.

37:32.100 --> 37:33.100
Stop!

37:33.100 --> 37:36.100
Don't kill her!

37:36.100 --> 37:42.100
Gagul, you deserve to die because you have murdered the Kolo Chief of our people.

37:42.100 --> 37:45.100
Then kill me.

37:45.100 --> 37:47.100
I am not afraid of death.

37:47.100 --> 37:48.100
No.

37:48.100 --> 37:52.100
A murder is not resolved by another murder.

37:52.100 --> 37:55.100
We will go back to our homeland.

37:55.100 --> 37:59.100
And we will both face the justice of the Kukwana people.

37:59.100 --> 38:04.100
They will decide who they want to be in Kolo Chief.

38:04.100 --> 38:06.100
Me or you?

38:06.100 --> 38:07.100
Take her away.

38:07.100 --> 38:09.100
I will join you later.

38:09.100 --> 38:10.100
Yes, yes.

38:10.100 --> 38:15.100
Sir Henry, you have been into Kona Suleiman.

38:15.100 --> 38:17.100
What did you find there?

38:17.100 --> 38:20.100
We found the body of my brother.

38:20.100 --> 38:22.100
I am sorry.

38:22.100 --> 38:24.100
And where is Captain Godwin?

38:24.100 --> 38:26.100
He was killed by a rockfall.

38:26.100 --> 38:30.100
You are a noble and a brave man, Sir Henry.

38:30.100 --> 38:32.100
You did what you had to do.

38:32.100 --> 38:33.100
Did I?

38:33.100 --> 38:35.100
I don't know.

38:35.100 --> 38:39.100
Of course, I mean, I want to leave this place immediately.

38:39.100 --> 38:41.100
We must return to Dublin.

38:41.100 --> 38:44.100
And how do you propose to do that, Sir Henry?

38:44.100 --> 38:49.100
You forget that we have no provisions and no one to guide us.

38:49.100 --> 38:54.100
I told you that only a fool would try to find King Solomon's minds.

38:54.100 --> 38:58.100
But there must be some way we can get back.

38:58.100 --> 39:02.100
If you can think of a way we can do that, then please tell me.

39:02.100 --> 39:07.100
Because I have no idea how we will do it.

39:07.100 --> 39:10.100
We will help you to return to Dublin.

39:10.100 --> 39:13.100
I will send five men with you.

39:13.100 --> 39:15.100
They will make sure you have food to eat.

39:15.100 --> 39:19.100
And they will protect you until you reach Sitala's Club.

39:23.100 --> 39:27.100
We made our way slowly and wearily back to Dublin.

39:27.100 --> 39:33.100
And we were almost dead with exhaustion when we finally reached my house.

39:34.100 --> 39:43.100
Sir Henry rested for a few days and returned home to England.

39:43.100 --> 39:48.100
When he left, I decided to write this account of what happened.

39:48.100 --> 39:53.100
I have seen the legendary King Solomon's minds.

39:53.100 --> 39:57.100
My son's future as a doctor is secure.

39:57.100 --> 40:05.100
But my health is not good and I don't expect to live much longer.

40:05.100 --> 40:12.100
Let this serve as a warning to anyone else who tries to find King Solomon's minds.

40:12.100 --> 40:18.100
You may not live to tell the tale.

40:27.100 --> 40:37.100
You may not live to tell the tale.

40:37.100 --> 40:42.100
You may not live to tell the tale.

40:57.100 --> 41:00.100
You may not live to tell the tale.

41:00.100 --> 41:03.100
You may not live to tell the tale.

41:03.100 --> 41:06.100
You may not live to tell the tale.

41:06.100 --> 41:08.100
You may not live to tell the tale.

41:08.100 --> 41:13.100
You may not live to tell the tale.

41:13.100 --> 41:17.100
How am I going to carry this water all the way to the village?

41:17.100 --> 41:20.100
I'm not surprised you have a pain in your back, Jata.

41:20.100 --> 41:23.100
It's all that time you spend lying down.

41:24.100 --> 41:27.100
That's such a bad thing to say.

41:28.100 --> 41:30.100
Be happy, Jata.

41:30.100 --> 41:33.100
Your husband is our chief, a great man.

41:33.100 --> 41:35.100
And he loves you.

41:35.100 --> 41:40.100
If one Jew really loved me, he would carry this bucket for me.

41:40.100 --> 41:43.100
No man would do that for a woman.

41:43.100 --> 41:45.100
Men are lazy.

41:45.100 --> 41:47.100
You are right, Mumbi.

41:47.100 --> 41:49.100
All men are lazy.

41:49.100 --> 41:52.100
But your husband is a lion among men.

41:52.100 --> 41:54.100
He looks after us well.

41:54.100 --> 41:56.100
Everyone loves him.

41:56.100 --> 41:58.100
Everyone except Jumbo.

41:58.100 --> 42:00.100
Jumbo, true.

42:00.100 --> 42:03.100
The medicine man is jealous of your husband.

42:03.100 --> 42:05.100
Everyone knows that.

42:05.100 --> 42:07.100
He wants to be chief.

42:07.100 --> 42:08.100
Yes.

42:08.100 --> 42:10.100
Don't worry, Jata.

42:10.100 --> 42:13.100
It will never happen.

42:13.100 --> 42:16.100
When Jiro is chief for life,

42:16.100 --> 42:19.100
Jumbo will never be chief.

42:19.100 --> 42:21.100
Come, let's go back.

42:23.100 --> 42:26.100
You know they are meeting this afternoon.

42:26.100 --> 42:27.100
Who?

42:27.100 --> 42:30.100
The chief, Jumbo and the other elders.

42:30.100 --> 42:31.100
Why?

42:31.100 --> 42:34.100
They will talk about Juan Jiro's idea.

42:34.100 --> 42:35.100
Oh, yes.

42:35.100 --> 42:38.100
The nature reserve.

42:38.100 --> 42:40.100
I don't understand.

42:40.100 --> 42:44.100
Around the village, there is land, there are animals.

42:44.100 --> 42:48.100
What is the difference if it is called a nature reserve?

42:48.100 --> 42:51.100
If it becomes a nature reserve,

42:51.100 --> 42:54.100
it means that the land will be protected.

42:54.100 --> 42:57.100
There will be wardens in Land Rover cars.

42:57.100 --> 43:01.100
They will make sure that poachers are kept off the land.

43:01.100 --> 43:03.100
But who will pay for all this?

43:03.100 --> 43:06.100
The aid development organization.

43:06.100 --> 43:09.100
It is an international organization

43:09.100 --> 43:11.100
which helps to improve our lives.

43:11.100 --> 43:15.100
Do you remember the white people who came to the village last month?

43:15.100 --> 43:17.100
Yes.

43:17.100 --> 43:19.100
Now I remember.

43:19.100 --> 43:23.100
So, do you think the nature reserve idea is a good one?

43:23.100 --> 43:25.100
Yes, I do.

43:25.100 --> 43:27.100
But Jumbo is against it.

43:27.100 --> 43:28.100
Why?

43:28.100 --> 43:32.100
These days, he is against everything that Juan Jiro suggests.

43:32.100 --> 43:37.100
Paul Juan Jiro, he tries so hard to be understanding

43:37.100 --> 43:40.100
and fair to everyone.

43:40.100 --> 43:43.100
But Jumbo makes that so difficult for him.

43:43.100 --> 43:45.100
And look!

43:45.100 --> 43:46.100
What is it?

43:46.100 --> 43:49.100
A cow, lying on the path.

43:53.100 --> 43:56.100
It is echinia's cow.

43:56.100 --> 43:57.100
Dead?

43:57.100 --> 43:59.100
Oh no.

43:59.100 --> 44:02.100
Poor echinia.

44:02.100 --> 44:05.100
But how was it killed?

44:05.100 --> 44:08.100
Look at those marks on its neck.

44:08.100 --> 44:11.100
It looks as if it was attacked by a lion.

44:11.100 --> 44:14.100
But when did this happen?

44:14.100 --> 44:18.100
It was not here when we came to the west three hours ago.

44:18.100 --> 44:21.100
We must warn the village.

44:21.100 --> 44:24.100
No, no, no.

44:26.100 --> 44:28.100
Jumbo!

44:28.100 --> 44:30.100
Jumbo!

44:30.100 --> 44:32.100
What is it, Jumbo?

44:32.100 --> 44:35.100
You must stop this plan now.

44:35.100 --> 44:38.100
We do not need a nature reserve here.

44:38.100 --> 44:42.100
Why must you always oppose me, Jumbo?

44:42.100 --> 44:46.100
Whatever I say, I can be sure you will suggest the opposite.

44:46.100 --> 44:51.100
It pleases you to say that, Juan Juro, but it is not true.

44:51.100 --> 44:53.100
Not true!

44:53.100 --> 44:57.100
Why are you against the idea of a nature reserve?

44:57.100 --> 44:59.100
It is perfect for us.

44:59.100 --> 45:03.100
It will protect our land and our animals, both the animals of the village

45:03.100 --> 45:05.100
and the animals in the wild.

45:05.100 --> 45:08.100
It will stop the poachers who are a real problem.

45:08.100 --> 45:13.100
I am tired of hearing of dead elephants killed for their tusks.

45:13.100 --> 45:14.100
I agree.

45:14.100 --> 45:16.100
The poachers must be stopped.

45:16.100 --> 45:18.100
You agree?

45:18.100 --> 45:21.100
You agree with something I say, I am amazed.

45:21.100 --> 45:24.100
There are other ways we can stop them.

45:24.100 --> 45:27.100
We do not need a nature reserve.

45:27.100 --> 45:29.100
Yes, we do.

45:29.100 --> 45:32.100
It is the best thing for us.

45:32.100 --> 45:37.100
We need trained people who can patrol our land and keep our animals safe from poachers.

45:37.100 --> 45:40.100
We can patrol the land ourselves.

45:40.100 --> 45:43.100
But there is no need to make our land a nature reserve.

45:43.100 --> 45:48.100
If we do that, we have to deal with the aid development organization.

45:48.100 --> 45:50.100
White people.

45:50.100 --> 45:53.100
White people do not understand our way of life.

45:53.100 --> 45:58.100
They will force us to do things their way, not our way.

45:58.100 --> 46:00.100
You are wrong, Jumbo.

46:00.100 --> 46:04.100
I had a meeting with the aid development people last week.

46:04.100 --> 46:06.100
They want nothing from us.

46:06.100 --> 46:10.100
They will give us money and let us make our own decisions.

46:10.100 --> 46:14.100
They will find some way to control us.

46:14.100 --> 46:16.100
What is your feeling, Runo?

46:16.100 --> 46:18.100
I agree with you, one Jumbo.

46:18.100 --> 46:19.100
Of course you do.

46:19.100 --> 46:21.100
You are one Juro's footstool.

46:21.100 --> 46:23.100
I will not forgive you for that, Jumbo.

46:23.100 --> 46:25.100
I am shaking with fear, Runo.

46:25.100 --> 46:28.100
Murithi, you've said nothing at all.

46:28.100 --> 46:30.100
What is your opinion?

46:30.100 --> 46:32.100
I agree with you, Jumbo.

46:32.100 --> 46:36.100
I am afraid the aid development people will control us.

46:36.100 --> 46:38.100
You see.

46:38.100 --> 46:41.100
We'll call a meeting of the whole village.

46:41.100 --> 46:47.100
You will find, Jumbo, that most people are in favor of the idea of a nature reserve.

46:47.100 --> 46:51.100
They will not be after they hear me speak.

46:51.100 --> 46:53.100
We shall see.

46:53.100 --> 46:59.100
Now, this cow that was found this morning on the path to the well, who has seen it?

46:59.100 --> 47:01.100
Mombi took me to see it.

47:01.100 --> 47:03.100
It looks as if it was killed by a lion.

47:03.100 --> 47:06.100
But it didn't eat any part of the cow.

47:06.100 --> 47:09.100
That is strange.

47:09.100 --> 47:11.100
This lion must be ill.

47:11.100 --> 47:14.100
We'll have to send out a search party to find it.

47:14.100 --> 47:16.100
Runo, will you lead it?

47:16.100 --> 47:18.100
Of course, one Juro.

47:18.100 --> 47:19.100
Good.

47:19.100 --> 47:21.100
The meeting is ended.

47:21.100 --> 47:23.100
Chief one Juro, wait.

47:23.100 --> 47:25.100
What is it, Murithi?

47:25.100 --> 47:27.100
Jumbo is in a trance.

47:27.100 --> 47:31.100
We must listen to his words.

47:31.100 --> 47:36.100
I see bad things coming.

47:36.100 --> 47:40.100
Many bad things are, tribe is in danger.

47:40.100 --> 47:43.100
I said the meeting is ended.

47:43.100 --> 47:44.100
What?

47:44.100 --> 47:45.100
Ended?

47:45.100 --> 47:47.100
Have you no respect for me?

47:47.100 --> 47:52.100
I am the medicine man, and you must listen when I speak.

47:52.100 --> 47:56.100
When you talk sense, then I will listen.

47:57.100 --> 48:09.100
He does not yet understand the power of magic, but he will.

48:09.100 --> 48:17.100
Momboko! Momboko!

48:17.100 --> 48:19.100
What is it, Chege?

48:19.100 --> 48:21.100
Where are you going?

48:21.100 --> 48:23.100
Some of our cows have disappeared.

48:23.100 --> 48:25.100
I have to find them.

48:26.100 --> 48:28.100
I will come with you.

48:28.100 --> 48:30.100
Why are you carrying a gun?

48:30.100 --> 48:32.100
Because of the lion.

48:32.100 --> 48:33.100
The lion?

48:33.100 --> 48:35.100
Are you planning to shoot it?

48:35.100 --> 48:36.100
Of course.

48:36.100 --> 48:38.100
Then I will be a hero in the village.

48:38.100 --> 48:42.100
And the lovely matter will fall in love with me.

48:43.100 --> 48:48.100
Seriously, Momboko, this is not a good idea.

48:48.100 --> 48:52.100
You know you have to get permission from my father, one Juro,

48:52.100 --> 48:54.100
before you kill a lion.

48:54.100 --> 48:55.100
You know that.

48:55.100 --> 48:58.100
I will only kill the lion if it attacks me.

48:58.100 --> 48:59.100
I am not stupid.

48:59.100 --> 49:01.100
We will have to be careful.

49:01.100 --> 49:02.100
Of course.

49:02.100 --> 49:05.100
But we also have to find the cows.

49:05.100 --> 49:07.100
How many are missing?

49:07.100 --> 49:08.100
Three.

49:08.100 --> 49:09.100
Chege.

49:09.100 --> 49:10.100
Look.

49:10.100 --> 49:11.100
What?

49:11.100 --> 49:12.100
Over there.

49:12.100 --> 49:13.100
A cow.

49:13.100 --> 49:14.100
Where?

49:14.100 --> 49:15.100
I can't see anything.

49:15.100 --> 49:17.100
It is lying on the ground.

49:17.100 --> 49:18.100
Come on.

49:19.100 --> 49:21.100
Is it dead?

49:21.100 --> 49:22.100
Yes.

49:22.100 --> 49:24.100
And look.

49:24.100 --> 49:26.100
The others are over there.

49:26.100 --> 49:27.100
Oh no.

49:27.100 --> 49:28.100
What was that?

49:28.100 --> 49:29.100
A lion.

49:29.100 --> 49:30.100
Where is it?

49:30.100 --> 49:32.100
I don't know.

49:32.100 --> 49:35.100
The noise is coming from over there.

49:35.100 --> 49:37.100
In those bushes.

49:37.100 --> 49:38.100
Chege.

49:38.100 --> 49:39.100
Oh no.

49:39.100 --> 49:40.100
What was that?

49:40.100 --> 49:41.100
A lion.

49:41.100 --> 49:42.100
Where is it?

49:42.100 --> 49:44.100
I don't know.

49:44.100 --> 49:47.100
The noise is coming from over there.

49:48.100 --> 49:49.100
Chege.

49:49.100 --> 49:51.100
We must kill it.

49:51.100 --> 49:56.100
We cannot kill a lion without the permission of my father.

49:56.100 --> 49:58.100
One zero will understand.

49:58.100 --> 50:00.100
Our animals are more important.

50:00.100 --> 50:01.100
Wait.

50:01.100 --> 50:05.100
Let me go back to the village and find him.

50:05.100 --> 50:06.100
No.

50:06.100 --> 50:07.100
Stop.

50:07.100 --> 50:09.100
I can see it.

50:09.100 --> 50:10.100
Where?

50:10.100 --> 50:11.100
There.

50:11.100 --> 50:13.100
In the bushes.

50:13.100 --> 50:16.100
I am going to shoot it.

50:16.100 --> 50:17.100
Go go.

50:17.100 --> 50:18.100
Stop.

50:18.100 --> 50:19.100
Why?

50:19.100 --> 50:20.100
The lion.

50:20.100 --> 50:23.100
I can see it now.

50:23.100 --> 50:25.100
It's white.

50:25.100 --> 50:27.100
A white lion?

50:27.100 --> 50:29.100
Are you sure?

50:29.100 --> 50:30.100
Yes.

50:30.100 --> 50:33.100
We cannot kill a white lion.

50:33.100 --> 50:37.100
We must go back and tell one zero what we have seen.

50:37.100 --> 50:38.100
Okay.

50:38.100 --> 50:40.100
Let us go.

50:40.100 --> 50:41.100
Quickly.

50:47.100 --> 50:49.100
Please.

50:49.100 --> 50:52.100
Close the door.

50:52.100 --> 51:02.100
You all know why I called this meeting.

51:02.100 --> 51:08.100
More of our animals have been killed and a lion has been seen.

51:08.100 --> 51:11.100
But a white lion.

51:11.100 --> 51:15.100
When was a white lion last seen in our land?

51:15.100 --> 51:16.100
Stop.

51:16.100 --> 51:19.100
What must we do?

51:19.100 --> 51:21.100
One zero.

51:21.100 --> 51:23.100
Please give us your commands.

51:23.100 --> 51:29.100
Even if the lion is a white lion, it must be killed.

51:29.100 --> 51:30.100
Mike.

51:30.100 --> 51:31.100
No.

51:31.100 --> 51:34.100
I have something to say.

51:34.100 --> 51:38.100
What is it, Chilmo?

51:38.100 --> 51:41.100
We cannot kill a white lion.

51:41.100 --> 51:43.100
It is forbidden.

51:43.100 --> 51:46.100
It has come for a reason.

51:46.100 --> 51:48.100
And what is this reason?

51:48.100 --> 51:51.100
We are being punished.

51:51.100 --> 51:58.100
Why do you think we are being punished, Chilmo?

51:58.100 --> 52:00.100
I do not know.

52:00.100 --> 52:03.100
But I will find out.

52:03.100 --> 52:06.100
Please tell us what you discover.

52:06.100 --> 52:09.100
In the meantime, I have an idea.

52:09.100 --> 52:14.100
Our friends from the aid development agency can help us.

52:14.100 --> 52:16.100
I have spoken with them.

52:16.100 --> 52:22.100
If we wish, they will go out in their land rovers and look for the lion.

52:22.100 --> 52:24.100
We do not need these white men.

52:24.100 --> 52:29.100
They have helped us before and they can help us again.

52:29.100 --> 52:31.100
What do our people think?

52:31.100 --> 52:35.100
Do you agree that I should ask the development workers to do this?

52:35.100 --> 52:36.100
Yes.

52:36.100 --> 52:37.100
Yes.

52:37.100 --> 52:38.100
Yes.

52:38.100 --> 52:39.100
Then it is agreed.

52:39.100 --> 52:41.100
I will ask them.

52:41.100 --> 52:44.100
And if they see the lion, do not let them shoot it.

52:44.100 --> 52:47.100
You will bring disaster to our people.

52:47.100 --> 52:49.100
They will not shoot it.

52:49.100 --> 52:53.100
But we must find it before more animals are killed.

52:53.100 --> 52:54.100
Yes.

52:54.100 --> 52:55.100
Right.

52:55.100 --> 52:56.100
Yes.

52:56.100 --> 52:57.100
Right.

53:06.100 --> 53:10.100
Runo, what do you want?

53:10.100 --> 53:13.100
I need to speak with you.

53:13.100 --> 53:14.100
Please.

53:14.100 --> 53:15.100
Come in.

53:15.100 --> 53:19.100
What do you want to talk to me about?

53:19.100 --> 53:22.100
You made fun of me at the last meeting.

53:22.100 --> 53:25.100
I am not happy about that.

53:25.100 --> 53:27.100
Let me apologize.

53:27.100 --> 53:29.100
Your apology is accepted.

53:29.100 --> 53:31.100
If it is real.

53:31.100 --> 53:32.100
Of course.

53:32.100 --> 53:34.100
I am a man of honor.

53:35.100 --> 53:37.100
Now tell me.

53:37.100 --> 53:39.100
Did you find the lion?

53:39.100 --> 53:40.100
No.

53:40.100 --> 53:43.100
We have searched all the forests around the village.

53:43.100 --> 53:45.100
It is very strange.

53:45.100 --> 53:47.100
There is no sign of a lion.

53:47.100 --> 53:49.100
No sign at all.

53:49.100 --> 53:52.100
And the white men in the Land Rover.

53:52.100 --> 53:54.100
They have found nothing either.

53:54.100 --> 53:58.100
There are no lions at all between here and Malinde.

53:58.100 --> 54:00.100
You will find nothing.

54:00.100 --> 54:03.100
Because this lion is a spirit.

54:03.100 --> 54:06.100
It can be seen or not seen.

54:06.100 --> 54:09.100
Visible or invisible.

54:09.100 --> 54:11.100
And when it is seen.

54:11.100 --> 54:15.100
It is seen in different places at the same time.

54:15.100 --> 54:16.100
What?

54:16.100 --> 54:18.100
How do you know?

54:18.100 --> 54:20.100
Many people have told me.

54:20.100 --> 54:24.100
Itumu, mukami, nukjogu and gary.

54:24.100 --> 54:29.100
They all saw it at the same time yesterday.

54:29.100 --> 54:31.100
Are you sure?

54:32.100 --> 54:34.100
Do you doubt the word of a medicine man?

54:34.100 --> 54:35.100
No.

54:35.100 --> 54:37.100
Of course not.

54:37.100 --> 54:39.100
But what are we to do?

54:39.100 --> 54:43.100
We have to discover why the lion is here.

54:43.100 --> 54:45.100
Then we will know what to do.

54:45.100 --> 54:49.100
And I have a plan.

54:49.100 --> 54:51.100
Someone is here to see you.

54:51.100 --> 54:52.100
Should I leave?

54:52.100 --> 54:53.100
No.

54:53.100 --> 54:54.100
Stay.

54:54.100 --> 54:56.100
I think it is Wakera.

54:56.100 --> 54:57.100
The daughter of Mumbi.

54:57.100 --> 54:59.100
Mumbi's daughter.

54:59.100 --> 55:02.100
She is only eight years old.

55:02.100 --> 55:04.100
Why is she visiting you?

55:04.100 --> 55:08.100
Small children can often see things we cannot see.

55:08.100 --> 55:12.100
She can help me find the answer to the mystery of the lion.

55:12.100 --> 55:14.100
Are you serious?

55:14.100 --> 55:18.100
You are going to ask a child to explain the mystery.

55:18.100 --> 55:23.100
Bruno, do not question the ways of the medicine man.

55:23.100 --> 55:27.100
Please let Wakera in.

55:27.100 --> 55:30.100
And stay to listen to what she has to say.

55:30.100 --> 55:33.100
Welcome, Wakera.

55:33.100 --> 55:36.100
You want to see me, Basa?

55:36.100 --> 55:41.100
Please, sit down here.

55:41.100 --> 55:45.100
Wakera, you see this bowl of water?

55:45.100 --> 55:47.100
Yes.

55:47.100 --> 55:52.100
With it, you can help me solve the mystery of the white lion.

55:52.100 --> 55:54.100
How?

55:55.100 --> 55:58.100
Hold the bowl in both hands.

55:58.100 --> 56:00.100
Look into the water.

56:00.100 --> 56:04.100
Tell me what you see.

56:04.100 --> 56:08.100
I can't see anything.

56:08.100 --> 56:10.100
Look again.

56:10.100 --> 56:11.100
Oh.

56:11.100 --> 56:14.100
Now, I can see a lion.

56:14.100 --> 56:16.100
What?

56:16.100 --> 56:19.100
What color is the lion, Wakera?

56:19.100 --> 56:21.100
White.

56:22.100 --> 56:25.100
Are you sure the lion is white?

56:25.100 --> 56:26.100
Yes.

56:26.100 --> 56:29.100
And he looks angry.

56:29.100 --> 56:30.100
Very angry.

56:30.100 --> 56:35.100
Wakera, ask the lion why he is angry.

56:35.100 --> 56:39.100
Why are you angry?

56:39.100 --> 56:42.100
He is angry with the chief.

56:42.100 --> 56:44.100
Angled with the chief?

56:44.100 --> 56:45.100
Yes.

56:45.100 --> 56:49.100
He says the chief is a bad man.

56:49.100 --> 56:50.100
What?

56:50.100 --> 56:53.100
A bad man?

56:53.100 --> 57:00.100
Oh.

57:00.100 --> 57:02.100
I'm frightened.

57:02.100 --> 57:04.100
I made the lion angry.

57:04.100 --> 57:06.100
Don't worry, Wakera.

57:06.100 --> 57:09.100
You have done very well.

57:09.100 --> 57:11.100
You can go now.

57:11.100 --> 57:13.100
But I cannot leave.

57:13.100 --> 57:15.100
The lion is near.

57:15.100 --> 57:18.100
Wait.

57:19.100 --> 57:21.100
It is safe now.

57:21.100 --> 57:22.100
Bruno?

57:22.100 --> 57:23.100
Yes.

57:23.100 --> 57:26.100
Will you take Wakera back to her home?

57:26.100 --> 57:28.100
Of course.

57:28.100 --> 57:33.100
Thank you.

57:33.100 --> 57:39.100
Murithi, you can come in now.

57:39.100 --> 57:41.100
Is everything all right?

57:41.100 --> 57:42.100
Yes.

57:42.100 --> 57:43.100
Well done.

57:43.100 --> 57:45.100
You did well.

57:45.100 --> 57:47.100
I did my best.

57:47.100 --> 57:49.100
Where is the recording machine?

57:49.100 --> 57:50.100
Here.

57:50.100 --> 57:53.100
When it is dark, take it to the cave.

57:53.100 --> 57:55.100
We do not need it anymore.

57:55.100 --> 57:57.100
The plan is going well, Murithi.

57:57.100 --> 58:00.100
But there is one thing I don't understand.

58:00.100 --> 58:03.100
Wakera saw nothing in her water.

58:03.100 --> 58:06.100
How did you persuade her to tell lies?

58:06.100 --> 58:12.100
I told her that she would grow into a beautiful woman if she helped me.

58:12.100 --> 58:14.100
Chummo, you should not lie to a child.

58:14.100 --> 58:16.100
It is for the greater good, Murithi.

58:16.100 --> 58:19.100
Soon the whole village will know that the chief is a bad man.

58:19.100 --> 58:24.100
And soon after that, you will be the new chief.

58:24.100 --> 58:26.100
Who is this?

58:26.100 --> 58:27.100
I don't know.

58:27.100 --> 58:29.100
We must not let them in.

58:29.100 --> 58:31.100
They must not see the recording machine.

58:31.100 --> 58:33.100
Leave by this door.

58:33.100 --> 58:34.100
Take the machine.

58:34.100 --> 58:36.100
Give it to me.

58:36.100 --> 58:38.100
Your phone!

58:38.100 --> 58:41.100
Chummo, are you there?

58:41.100 --> 58:43.100
Quickly.

58:44.100 --> 58:47.100
Chummo, you are here.

58:47.100 --> 58:49.100
And you, Murithi.

58:49.100 --> 58:52.100
Why didn't you answer when I called?

58:52.100 --> 58:55.100
And what is that machine?

58:55.100 --> 58:56.100
Mumbi.

58:57.100 --> 59:00.100
Did you know that four cows have been killed now?

59:00.100 --> 59:01.100
Yes.

59:01.100 --> 59:04.100
Everyone is sure that a lion is responsible.

59:04.100 --> 59:06.100
A white lion.

59:06.100 --> 59:10.100
But, white lions never come to this part of the country.

59:10.100 --> 59:12.100
What is that machine?

59:12.100 --> 59:13.100
Mumbi.

59:13.100 --> 59:16.100
Did you know that four cows have been killed now?

59:16.100 --> 59:17.100
Yes.

59:17.100 --> 59:20.100
Everyone is sure that a lion is responsible.

59:20.100 --> 59:22.100
A white lion.

59:22.100 --> 59:26.100
But, white lions never come to this part of the country.

59:26.100 --> 59:27.100
I know.

59:27.100 --> 59:29.100
It is strange.

59:29.100 --> 59:30.100
Oh, Jata.

59:30.100 --> 59:31.100
Look.

59:31.100 --> 59:33.100
Someone is coming to the well.

59:33.100 --> 59:34.100
Who is it?

59:34.100 --> 59:37.100
I think it's Bruno.

59:37.100 --> 59:38.100
Bruno?

59:38.100 --> 59:40.100
Coming to the well?

59:40.100 --> 59:43.100
Maybe his wife has sent him to get water.

59:43.100 --> 59:47.100
Now that is not possible.

59:47.100 --> 59:48.100
Bruno.

59:48.100 --> 59:51.100
Why are you coming to the well?

59:51.100 --> 59:54.100
Are you going to carry water home for your wife?

59:54.100 --> 59:57.100
He doesn't look very happy.

59:57.100 --> 59:58.100
Bruno.

59:58.100 --> 01:00:01.100
Why are you looking so serious?

01:00:01.100 --> 01:00:02.100
Jata.

01:00:02.100 --> 01:00:04.100
I need to speak to you.

01:00:04.100 --> 01:00:06.100
Speak to me then.

01:00:06.100 --> 01:00:09.100
I have some bad news.

01:00:09.100 --> 01:00:11.100
What's the matter?

01:00:11.100 --> 01:00:12.100
The lion.

01:00:12.100 --> 01:00:13.100
Oh no.

01:00:13.100 --> 01:00:15.100
There are more dead animals?

01:00:15.100 --> 01:00:16.100
No.

01:00:16.100 --> 01:00:18.100
Not animals.

01:00:19.100 --> 01:00:20.100
No.

01:00:20.100 --> 01:00:22.100
What has happened then?

01:00:22.100 --> 01:00:23.100
Jata.

01:00:23.100 --> 01:00:25.100
You must please come with me.

01:00:25.100 --> 01:00:26.100
What's wrong?

01:00:26.100 --> 01:00:28.100
What's happened?

01:00:28.100 --> 01:00:30.100
The lion has killed again.

01:00:30.100 --> 01:00:32.100
But this time...

01:00:32.100 --> 01:00:34.100
This time?

01:00:34.100 --> 01:00:35.100
Tell me.

01:00:35.100 --> 01:00:36.100
Not...

01:00:36.100 --> 01:00:37.100
Not one jiro.

01:00:37.100 --> 01:00:38.100
No.

01:00:38.100 --> 01:00:40.100
It is not one jiro.

01:00:40.100 --> 01:00:42.100
Then who?

01:00:42.100 --> 01:00:44.100
It is Chege.

01:00:44.100 --> 01:00:46.100
Chege!

01:00:47.100 --> 01:00:48.100
My son!

01:00:48.100 --> 01:00:49.100
Where?

01:00:49.100 --> 01:00:54.100
He is in the field of yams outside the village.

01:00:54.100 --> 01:00:55.100
Oh!

01:00:55.100 --> 01:00:56.100
No.

01:00:56.100 --> 01:01:01.100
The lion has killed my son.

01:01:01.100 --> 01:01:04.100
Even if it is a white lion.

01:01:04.100 --> 01:01:06.100
I will kill it.

01:01:06.100 --> 01:01:09.100
I will kill it with my bare hands.

01:01:09.100 --> 01:01:12.100
Oh, Chege!

01:01:17.100 --> 01:01:26.100
Where is she?

01:01:26.100 --> 01:01:28.100
Where is Jata?

01:01:28.100 --> 01:01:29.100
Inside.

01:01:29.100 --> 01:01:37.100
Jata.

01:01:37.100 --> 01:01:38.100
Jata.

01:01:38.100 --> 01:01:39.100
I'm here.

01:01:39.100 --> 01:01:40.100
Speak to me.

01:01:40.100 --> 01:01:42.100
Why, Chege?

01:01:43.100 --> 01:01:45.100
He was so good.

01:01:45.100 --> 01:01:46.100
So fine.

01:01:46.100 --> 01:01:50.100
This holy lion ripped out my son's heart.

01:01:50.100 --> 01:01:52.100
I want to die.

01:01:52.100 --> 01:01:54.100
I want to die too.

01:01:54.100 --> 01:01:57.100
You know what they are saying.

01:01:57.100 --> 01:02:01.100
That it's punishing our tribe because of your actions.

01:02:01.100 --> 01:02:04.100
The child wakira saw it in the water.

01:02:04.100 --> 01:02:06.100
But I've done only good.

01:02:06.100 --> 01:02:09.100
I've brought water to our fields.

01:02:09.100 --> 01:02:12.100
Because of this, our crops grow well.

01:02:12.100 --> 01:02:17.100
Then maybe it's because you are dealing with white men.

01:02:17.100 --> 01:02:18.100
Whatever it is.

01:02:18.100 --> 01:02:23.100
It's too late for my son.

01:02:40.100 --> 01:02:41.100
Here they come.

01:02:41.100 --> 01:02:43.100
Wanjiro and Jata.

01:02:43.100 --> 01:02:45.100
Poor Jata.

01:02:45.100 --> 01:02:47.100
She looks ready to die.

01:02:47.100 --> 01:02:49.100
Poor Wanjiro.

01:02:49.100 --> 01:02:51.100
His oldest son.

01:02:51.100 --> 01:02:55.100
The meeting started.

01:02:55.100 --> 01:02:58.100
Let us begin.

01:02:58.100 --> 01:03:01.100
You have all heard the news.

01:03:01.100 --> 01:03:04.100
Wanjiro, Jata.

01:03:04.100 --> 01:03:07.100
Words cannot express our grief.

01:03:07.100 --> 01:03:10.100
We are grieving with you.

01:03:10.100 --> 01:03:13.100
Thank you, my friends.

01:03:13.100 --> 01:03:16.100
It's time to take action.

01:03:16.100 --> 01:03:18.100
What should we do, Wanjiro?

01:03:18.100 --> 01:03:21.100
Find this animal and kill it.

01:03:21.100 --> 01:03:22.100
Wanjiro.

01:03:22.100 --> 01:03:24.100
What is it, Jumbo?

01:03:24.100 --> 01:03:29.100
First, please accept my sorrow at the death of your son, Chege.

01:03:29.100 --> 01:03:31.100
Thank you, Jumbo.

01:03:31.100 --> 01:03:33.100
But I have to repeat.

01:03:33.100 --> 01:03:37.100
The animal which killed your son is a white lion.

01:03:37.100 --> 01:03:44.100
The white lion is a spirit who has come to punish us because of our evil deeds.

01:03:44.100 --> 01:03:49.100
In fact, because of your evil deeds, Wanjiro.

01:03:49.100 --> 01:03:51.100
What is my shield?

01:03:51.100 --> 01:03:54.100
I don't know what you think you are saying, but...

01:03:54.100 --> 01:03:57.100
I will tell you, Wanjiro.

01:03:57.100 --> 01:04:02.100
The lion is punishing us because of your dealings with the white man.

01:04:02.100 --> 01:04:05.100
Please explain your meaning, Jumbo.

01:04:05.100 --> 01:04:07.100
Listen to my words, everyone.

01:04:07.100 --> 01:04:10.100
Chief Wanjiro wants to build a natural reserve.

01:04:10.100 --> 01:04:12.100
We all know this, Jumbo.

01:04:12.100 --> 01:04:15.100
But there is something you do not know.

01:04:15.100 --> 01:04:20.100
Chief Wanjiro has made a secret arrangement with the white men.

01:04:20.100 --> 01:04:30.100
He plans to sell them land near the coast so that they can build an airport, roads, hotels,

01:04:30.100 --> 01:04:34.100
and expensive places that only foreigners can afford.

01:04:34.100 --> 01:04:40.100
This is a secret plan and the white men will pay Wanjiro for this!

01:04:40.100 --> 01:04:41.100
What?

01:04:41.100 --> 01:04:42.100
What?

01:04:42.100 --> 01:04:45.100
What do you have of this nonsense, Jumbo?

01:04:45.100 --> 01:04:47.100
You met with these men last week?

01:04:47.100 --> 01:04:48.100
Yes.

01:04:48.100 --> 01:04:50.100
Everyone knows that.

01:04:50.100 --> 01:04:54.100
Someone else from our people was at that meeting.

01:04:54.100 --> 01:04:55.100
Yes.

01:04:55.100 --> 01:04:58.100
Murithi was with me when I met them.

01:04:58.100 --> 01:05:03.100
Murithi, tell the rest of us about the meeting.

01:05:03.100 --> 01:05:07.100
It is exactly as Jumbo said.

01:05:07.100 --> 01:05:11.100
You thought I would stay silent if the white men paid me enough.

01:05:11.100 --> 01:05:13.100
But you were wrong.

01:05:13.100 --> 01:05:15.100
What are you doing?

01:05:15.100 --> 01:05:18.100
Murithi, what are you saying?

01:05:18.100 --> 01:05:21.100
It is time for you to go, Wanjiro.

01:05:21.100 --> 01:05:24.100
You and Jata are in disgrace.

01:05:24.100 --> 01:05:27.100
You must leave the village.

01:05:27.100 --> 01:05:32.100
What are you doing?

01:05:32.100 --> 01:05:33.100
Hello?

01:05:33.100 --> 01:05:35.100
Jum, it's Mike.

01:05:35.100 --> 01:05:36.100
Hi, Mike.

01:05:36.100 --> 01:05:38.100
How's it going?

01:05:38.100 --> 01:05:40.100
Did you get to see Chief Wanjiro today?

01:05:40.100 --> 01:05:42.100
No, I didn't.

01:05:42.100 --> 01:05:46.100
Listen, Jum, something strange is going on down there.

01:05:46.100 --> 01:05:50.100
Wanjiro has been sent out of the village in disgrace.

01:05:50.100 --> 01:05:51.100
What?

01:05:51.100 --> 01:05:52.100
Why?

01:05:52.100 --> 01:05:54.100
I've been trying to find out.

01:05:54.100 --> 01:05:59.100
What I do know is that a guy called Murithi is the new chief.

01:05:59.100 --> 01:06:01.100
But the medicine man...

01:06:01.100 --> 01:06:02.100
Jumbo?

01:06:02.100 --> 01:06:04.100
Yeah, that's him.

01:06:04.100 --> 01:06:06.100
He's the one who's really in charge.

01:06:06.100 --> 01:06:09.100
And he doesn't want to have anything to do with us.

01:06:09.100 --> 01:06:11.100
Oh, no.

01:06:11.100 --> 01:06:13.100
This is terrible.

01:06:13.100 --> 01:06:15.100
All that work wasted.

01:06:15.100 --> 01:06:17.100
Where is Wanjiro?

01:06:17.100 --> 01:06:20.100
He and his wife have moved into an apartment here in Malindi.

01:06:21.100 --> 01:06:23.100
An apartment in the town?

01:06:23.100 --> 01:06:25.100
For a village tribal chief?

01:06:25.100 --> 01:06:26.100
Yes.

01:06:26.100 --> 01:06:28.100
But there's something else.

01:06:28.100 --> 01:06:31.100
I was in the main street of Malindi this morning.

01:06:31.100 --> 01:06:33.100
And I saw Jumbo.

01:06:33.100 --> 01:06:36.100
You saw Jumbo in town?

01:06:36.100 --> 01:06:37.100
Yes.

01:06:37.100 --> 01:06:39.100
I've seen him here a few times.

01:06:39.100 --> 01:06:44.100
But this morning, I saw him talking to a couple of South African guys.

01:06:44.100 --> 01:06:47.100
Tim Hawkins and Monty Klein.

01:06:47.100 --> 01:06:48.100
I don't know them.

01:06:48.100 --> 01:06:49.100
Do you?

01:06:49.100 --> 01:06:50.100
Not personally.

01:06:50.100 --> 01:06:51.100
No.

01:06:51.100 --> 01:06:53.100
But I know who they are.

01:06:53.100 --> 01:06:57.100
They've both been in prison for illegal ivory trading.

01:06:57.100 --> 01:06:59.100
My God.

01:06:59.100 --> 01:07:01.100
What do you think we should do?

01:07:01.100 --> 01:07:05.100
Well, first of all, we should go and see Wanjiro.

01:07:05.100 --> 01:07:06.100
I agree.

01:07:06.100 --> 01:07:08.100
I'll come and pick you up.

01:07:18.100 --> 01:07:25.100
Hello, Jada.

01:07:25.100 --> 01:07:34.100
Runo, hello, come in.

01:07:34.100 --> 01:07:37.100
Is Wanjiro here?

01:07:37.100 --> 01:07:38.100
Yes.

01:07:38.100 --> 01:07:40.100
Follow me.

01:07:40.100 --> 01:07:43.100
Wanjiro.

01:07:43.100 --> 01:07:47.100
Runo, this is an unexpected pleasure.

01:07:47.100 --> 01:07:49.100
Come in and sit down.

01:07:49.100 --> 01:07:51.100
I will bring some water.

01:07:51.100 --> 01:07:52.100
Thank you.

01:07:52.100 --> 01:07:53.100
This.

01:07:53.100 --> 01:07:56.100
This must be very difficult for you, Chief.

01:07:56.100 --> 01:07:57.100
To live here.

01:07:57.100 --> 01:07:58.100
Like this.

01:07:58.100 --> 01:08:00.100
Well, all right.

01:08:00.100 --> 01:08:02.100
Tell me your news.

01:08:02.100 --> 01:08:05.100
Moritha has been elected, Chief.

01:08:05.100 --> 01:08:06.100
Moritha.

01:08:06.100 --> 01:08:07.100
Hmm.

01:08:07.100 --> 01:08:09.100
Interesting.

01:08:09.100 --> 01:08:12.100
But Jumbo is the one with the power, no doubt.

01:08:12.100 --> 01:08:14.100
Runo.

01:08:14.100 --> 01:08:16.100
I have to ask you something.

01:08:16.100 --> 01:08:22.100
Did you believe Morithi's story that I secretly agreed to sell land to the white men?

01:08:22.100 --> 01:08:25.100
Do you believe that I would do that?

01:08:25.100 --> 01:08:27.100
After all the years, you've known me.

01:08:27.100 --> 01:08:31.100
Do you believe me or do you believe Morithi?

01:08:31.100 --> 01:08:33.100
No, Chief.

01:08:33.100 --> 01:08:35.100
But why would he...

01:08:35.100 --> 01:08:37.100
You can't see why he would lie.

01:08:37.100 --> 01:08:38.100
No.

01:08:38.100 --> 01:08:39.100
Neither can I.

01:08:39.100 --> 01:08:42.100
Goodness.

01:08:42.100 --> 01:08:44.100
So many visitors today.

01:08:44.100 --> 01:08:45.100
Oh.

01:08:45.100 --> 01:08:46.100
Hi.

01:08:46.100 --> 01:08:48.100
We're here to see the check.

01:08:48.100 --> 01:08:50.100
Oh, I'll take this one. Follow me, please.

01:08:50.100 --> 01:08:51.100
Of course.

01:08:51.100 --> 01:08:52.100
Thank you.

01:08:52.100 --> 01:08:56.100
Juan Jiro, the men from the aid development are here.

01:08:56.100 --> 01:08:58.100
Mike, hello.

01:08:58.100 --> 01:09:00.100
So good to see you.

01:09:00.100 --> 01:09:02.100
Hello, Juan Jiro.

01:09:02.100 --> 01:09:05.100
This is Runo, one of my oldest friends.

01:09:05.100 --> 01:09:06.100
Please to meet you, Runo.

01:09:06.100 --> 01:09:08.100
This is my colleague, Jim Ray.

01:09:08.100 --> 01:09:09.100
Hi.

01:09:09.100 --> 01:09:13.100
Juan Jiro, I have something important to tell you.

01:09:13.100 --> 01:09:16.100
Can we speak privately for a moment?

01:09:16.100 --> 01:09:20.100
Mike, anything you want to say, you can say in front of Runo.

01:09:20.100 --> 01:09:22.100
Okay.

01:09:22.100 --> 01:09:24.100
I have some news for you.

01:09:24.100 --> 01:09:27.100
I saw Chumbo this morning, here in Melinde.

01:09:27.100 --> 01:09:28.100
Really?

01:09:28.100 --> 01:09:30.100
What was he doing?

01:09:30.100 --> 01:09:33.100
He was talking to a couple of South Africans.

01:09:33.100 --> 01:09:39.100
They're criminals, lawbreakers, a couple of poachers who are well known to the police.

01:09:39.100 --> 01:09:43.100
They make their money selling elephant tusks on the black market.

01:09:43.100 --> 01:09:45.100
This is unbelievable.

01:09:45.100 --> 01:09:47.100
Of course.

01:09:47.100 --> 01:09:49.100
Now it all makes sense.

01:09:49.100 --> 01:09:53.100
This is why Chumbo was against the nature reserve.

01:09:53.100 --> 01:09:58.100
If we have a nature reserve, the land will be patrolled by wardens,

01:09:58.100 --> 01:10:01.100
and poachers will have a difficult time.

01:10:01.100 --> 01:10:03.100
We have no proof of this, of course.

01:10:03.100 --> 01:10:05.100
No, that's right.

01:10:05.100 --> 01:10:08.100
But this is going to affect us, too.

01:10:08.100 --> 01:10:12.100
So, we're planning to keep an eye on Chumbo for the next few days.

01:10:12.100 --> 01:10:14.100
Yes, please do that.

01:10:14.100 --> 01:10:16.100
I will help you.

01:10:16.100 --> 01:10:17.100
Thank you, Runo.

01:10:17.100 --> 01:10:20.100
It is the least I can do for an old friend.

01:10:25.100 --> 01:10:27.100
It's good of you to help us, Runo.

01:10:27.100 --> 01:10:30.100
We've invested a lot of money in this project.

01:10:30.100 --> 01:10:35.100
If the people in the village tell us to leave, it will all be wasted.

01:10:35.100 --> 01:10:38.100
Most people are thankful for the work you have done.

01:10:38.100 --> 01:10:40.100
I'm glad to hear it.

01:10:40.100 --> 01:10:41.100
Okay.

01:10:41.100 --> 01:10:44.100
You want us to drop you away from the village, right?

01:10:44.100 --> 01:10:45.100
Yes.

01:10:45.100 --> 01:10:48.100
I prefer to work the last few miles by myself.

01:10:48.100 --> 01:10:49.100
Okay.

01:10:49.100 --> 01:10:54.100
Where are you going, Mike? You took a wrong turning there.

01:10:54.100 --> 01:10:55.100
Did I?

01:10:55.100 --> 01:10:57.100
Is this the wrong way, Runo?

01:10:57.100 --> 01:11:02.100
Well, it is also possible to get to the village down this road.

01:11:02.100 --> 01:11:05.100
So, what's down here?

01:11:05.100 --> 01:11:09.100
It leads to the Nakuro cave, a very sacred place.

01:11:09.100 --> 01:11:14.100
No one except the chief and the medicine man are allowed to visit it.

01:11:14.100 --> 01:11:15.100
I see.

01:11:19.100 --> 01:11:21.100
Boy, this is a rough road.

01:11:21.100 --> 01:11:24.100
What's that light up ahead?

01:11:24.100 --> 01:11:28.100
But, that is where the cave is.

01:11:28.100 --> 01:11:30.100
But there should be no light there.

01:11:31.100 --> 01:11:33.100
Maybe we should take a look.

01:11:41.100 --> 01:11:44.100
Let's go and see what's going on.

01:11:48.100 --> 01:11:49.100
We are here.

01:11:49.100 --> 01:11:51.100
The Nakuro cave.

01:11:51.100 --> 01:11:54.100
Well, there's no one here now.

01:11:54.100 --> 01:11:57.100
But there was someone here a while ago.

01:11:58.100 --> 01:12:00.100
There's a fire burning.

01:12:00.100 --> 01:12:02.100
Let's take a look around.

01:12:02.100 --> 01:12:03.100
Look at this.

01:12:03.100 --> 01:12:04.100
What is it?

01:12:04.100 --> 01:12:06.100
It's a lion's head mass.

01:12:06.100 --> 01:12:10.100
And this thing next to it looks like an old rug.

01:12:10.100 --> 01:12:11.100
Phew.

01:12:11.100 --> 01:12:13.100
What a smell.

01:12:13.100 --> 01:12:16.100
This is the coat of a lion.

01:12:16.100 --> 01:12:18.100
Are you sure?

01:12:18.100 --> 01:12:20.100
Lion coats aren't this color.

01:12:20.100 --> 01:12:23.100
This is creamy white.

01:12:24.100 --> 01:12:25.100
Wow.

01:12:25.100 --> 01:12:26.100
Of course.

01:12:26.100 --> 01:12:27.100
The white lion.

01:12:27.100 --> 01:12:29.100
And look at this.

01:12:29.100 --> 01:12:31.100
A huge tape recorder.

01:12:37.100 --> 01:12:38.100
Jesus.

01:12:38.100 --> 01:12:39.100
Did you hear that?

01:12:39.100 --> 01:12:41.100
A white lion's coat.

01:12:41.100 --> 01:12:45.100
And a tape recording of a roaring lion.

01:12:45.100 --> 01:12:50.100
I think we should take these things and show them to the people in the village.

01:12:50.100 --> 01:12:51.100
Come on.

01:12:54.100 --> 01:13:03.100
People, welcome to my first meeting as your new chief.

01:13:03.100 --> 01:13:07.100
I want to tell you my plans for the future of the village.

01:13:07.100 --> 01:13:08.100
Hey, sir.

01:13:08.100 --> 01:13:09.100
What is that noise?

01:13:09.100 --> 01:13:16.100
Who is there?

01:13:16.100 --> 01:13:20.100
The white men are here in the Land Rover.

01:13:21.100 --> 01:13:22.100
The white men?

01:13:22.100 --> 01:13:23.100
How dare they?

01:13:23.100 --> 01:13:24.100
And Bruno is with them.

01:13:24.100 --> 01:13:25.100
Oh, where are those?

01:13:25.100 --> 01:13:28.100
They're coming here to the meeting.

01:13:28.100 --> 01:13:30.100
Don't let them in.

01:13:30.100 --> 01:13:31.100
Chumble.

01:13:31.100 --> 01:13:33.100
Please don't say that.

01:13:33.100 --> 01:13:35.100
We must let them in.

01:13:35.100 --> 01:13:38.100
Should I open the door and let them in?

01:13:38.100 --> 01:13:39.100
Yes.

01:13:39.100 --> 01:13:40.100
Yes.

01:13:40.100 --> 01:13:41.100
Let them in.

01:13:43.100 --> 01:13:48.100
Greetings, chief Morithi and medicine man Chumble.

01:13:49.100 --> 01:13:50.100
What do you want?

01:13:50.100 --> 01:13:54.100
We have come to pay our respects to the new chief.

01:13:54.100 --> 01:13:58.100
Well, you can do this and then you can leave.

01:13:58.100 --> 01:13:59.100
Okay.

01:13:59.100 --> 01:14:00.100
We'll do that.

01:14:00.100 --> 01:14:05.100
But first, we want to show you some things that we found at the Nakuro Cave.

01:14:05.100 --> 01:14:06.100
Michael!

01:14:06.100 --> 01:14:07.100
No.

01:14:07.100 --> 01:14:10.100
You have been to the Nakuro Cave?

01:14:10.100 --> 01:14:11.100
Yes.

01:14:11.100 --> 01:14:12.100
We have.

01:14:12.100 --> 01:14:15.100
Bruno, you had no right to go there.

01:14:15.100 --> 01:14:19.100
The Nakuro Cave is a sacred place for our people.

01:14:19.100 --> 01:14:21.100
If you took them there, you will be punished.

01:14:21.100 --> 01:14:29.100
Well, before you decide on Bruno's punishment, take a look at this lion's head mask, Michael.

01:14:29.100 --> 01:14:34.100
And this lion's coat, which has been painted white.

01:14:34.100 --> 01:14:36.100
And we also found this tape recorder.

01:14:36.100 --> 01:14:44.100
Let's listen to the tape, shall we?

01:14:44.100 --> 01:14:45.100
What?

01:14:45.100 --> 01:14:46.100
What are you doing?

01:14:46.100 --> 01:14:47.100
What are you doing?

01:14:47.100 --> 01:14:48.100
Sorry.

01:14:48.100 --> 01:14:53.100
You see, the white men were responsible for the white lion.

01:14:53.100 --> 01:14:55.100
They tried to trick us.

01:14:55.100 --> 01:14:57.100
No, Chumble.

01:14:57.100 --> 01:15:00.100
You and Morithi are the guilty ones.

01:15:00.100 --> 01:15:07.100
You and your South African friends who have been killing elephants and stealing their tusks for ivory.

01:15:07.100 --> 01:15:14.100
You are the ones who killed Chege and sent when Jiro into exile for crimes he did not commit.

01:15:14.100 --> 01:15:15.100
It was Chumble.

01:15:15.100 --> 01:15:16.100
He killed Chege.

01:15:16.100 --> 01:15:17.100
What are you doing?

01:15:17.100 --> 01:15:18.100
Fire!

01:15:18.100 --> 01:15:19.100
Fire!

01:15:19.100 --> 01:15:21.100
Bruno is trying to escape.

01:15:21.100 --> 01:15:22.100
Stop here.

01:15:22.100 --> 01:15:23.100
Don't worry.

01:15:23.100 --> 01:15:24.100
He won't get far.

01:15:24.100 --> 01:15:26.100
The police are here.

01:15:26.100 --> 01:15:27.100
Stop.

01:15:27.100 --> 01:15:28.100
You are under arrest.

01:15:28.100 --> 01:15:29.100
Stop.

01:15:30.100 --> 01:15:31.100
Ahh!

01:15:31.100 --> 01:15:32.100
Oh, my God!

01:15:32.100 --> 01:15:33.100
Oh, my God!

01:15:55.100 --> 01:15:56.100
One Jiro is back.

01:15:57.100 --> 01:16:00.100
Welcome back, one Jiro.

01:16:00.100 --> 01:16:01.100
Welcome Jata.

01:16:01.100 --> 01:16:02.100
Thank you, Bruno.

01:16:02.100 --> 01:16:04.100
It is good to be back.

01:16:04.100 --> 01:16:05.100
Yes.

01:16:05.100 --> 01:16:06.100
Home again.

01:16:06.100 --> 01:16:08.100
It is a good feeling.

01:16:08.100 --> 01:16:10.100
And Chumble and Morithi.

01:16:10.100 --> 01:16:12.100
What happened to them?

01:16:12.100 --> 01:16:13.100
Morithi was arrested.

01:16:13.100 --> 01:16:16.100
You will face trial for murder.

01:16:16.100 --> 01:16:18.100
And Chumble?

01:16:18.100 --> 01:16:20.100
He tried to escape from the police.

01:16:20.100 --> 01:16:25.100
And the police officer fired at him and shot him in the shoulder.

01:16:25.100 --> 01:16:28.100
And then he ran into the forest.

01:16:28.100 --> 01:16:29.100
I see.

01:16:29.100 --> 01:16:31.100
Did the police find him?

01:16:31.100 --> 01:16:32.100
No.

01:16:32.100 --> 01:16:34.100
Mumbi found him the next morning.

01:16:34.100 --> 01:16:35.100
Near the well.

01:16:35.100 --> 01:16:37.100
He was dead.

01:16:37.100 --> 01:16:38.100
Dead?

01:16:38.100 --> 01:16:39.100
Yes.

01:16:39.100 --> 01:16:43.100
Mumbi said it looked as if he had been attacked by a lion.

01:16:43.100 --> 01:16:46.100
A real lion this time.

